{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Besides building robust models, IRT models demonstrated the capability to enhance the performance of AES models in both convolutional recurrent neural networks and BERT (Uto et al. 2023).",
    "Incorporating neural coherence features: Farag et al. (2018) highlighted the limitation of convolutional recurrent neural network AES models when faced with adversarially crafted grammatically correct inputs consisting of incoherent sequences of sentences.",
    "Several AES studies have suggested integrating coherence features to enhance model performance and detect such adversarially crafted texts.",
    "Mesgar and Strube (2018) proposed a local coherence model that identifies salient information and extracts patterns of changes as a text progresses.",
    "The model captures the representation of salient information by measuring the similarity between LSTM hidden states of adjacent sentences."
  ],
